those are the two things.

00:33:06.680 --> 00:33:08.875
And all the different
forms of it.

00:33:08.875 --> 00:33:11.990
So, high fructose corn syrup,
all the different sweeteners

00:33:11.990 --> 00:33:14.336
and fillers, and Splenda,
and all that other stuff,

00:33:14.336 --> 00:33:15.710
is probably the
number one thing.

00:33:15.710 --> 00:33:17.595
There is sugar in everything.

00:33:17.595 --> 00:33:19.220
So sugar is probably
one of the biggest

00:33:19.220 --> 00:33:21.980
culprits for the
obesity crisis, I think.

00:33:21.980 --> 00:33:24.380
And when you go back and
look at food manufacturing

00:33:24.380 --> 00:33:25.945
and you look at what changed.

00:33:25.945 --> 00:33:27.320
There are a couple
of things that

00:33:27.320 --> 00:33:29.600
changed 30 to 40 years ago.

00:33:29.600 --> 00:33:32.150
The amount of sugar and
sweeteners is one of them.

00:33:32.150 --> 00:33:34.320
The amount of additives
and salt is another.

00:33:34.320 --> 00:33:37.370
The third is the use of certain
pesticides and chemicals

00:33:37.370 --> 00:33:38.690
in our food manufacturing.

00:33:38.690 --> 00:33:41.720
Those are probably your
three biggest changes.

