cross-contamination,

00:34:15.409 --> 00:34:18.666
that you're still getting
exposed to different chemicals,

00:34:18.666 --> 00:34:20.290
different pesticides,
different things.

00:34:20.290 --> 00:34:22.839
So, again, that's
why being proactive

00:34:22.839 --> 00:34:25.130
and being in the sort of
integrative functional space I

00:34:25.130 --> 00:34:26.094
think is so critical.

00:34:26.094 --> 00:34:28.010
Because it's hard to
control your environment.

00:34:28.010 --> 00:34:31.110
Even when you're being so
conscious, and so careful,

00:34:31.110 --> 00:34:32.929
and so deliberate
about your choices.

00:34:32.929 --> 00:34:34.489
Sometimes it's
very difficult just

00:34:34.489 --> 00:34:35.630
to control the environment.

00:34:35.630 --> 00:34:38.360
And our needs are different
than what they were.

00:34:38.360 --> 00:34:42.050
We had an infectious disease
problem, maybe 50 years ago.

00:34:42.050 --> 00:34:44.330
We had different medical issues.

00:34:44.330 --> 00:34:46.130
The medical issues
of tomorrow are

00:34:46.130 --> 00:34:48.020
going to be environmentally
induced, they're

00:34:48.020 --> 00:34:50.540
going to be toxicity
issues, they're going

00:34:50.540 --> 00:34:52.310
to be diseases of inflammation.

00:34:52.310 --> 00:34:54.210
Those are the diseases
of today and tomorrow.

00:34:54.210 --> 00:34:55.835
That's why cancer's
on the rise, that's

00:34:55.835 --> 00:34:57.750
why autoimmune disease
