00:45:59.599 --> 00:46:02.270
Looking at estrogen,
progesterone, thyroid.

00:46:02.270 --> 00:46:03.744
The derivatives
of those hormones

00:46:03.744 --> 00:46:06.160
because then it tells us what
your body's doing with them.

00:46:06.160 --> 00:46:08.132
And you want to do
them periodically.

00:46:08.132 --> 00:46:09.340
Because you want to track it.

00:46:09.340 --> 00:46:11.500
Speaking of data, you want
to be able to track it.

00:46:11.500 --> 00:46:13.666
Because what's normal for
you, is not normal for me.

00:46:13.666 --> 00:46:16.330
So you know you might feel
really good at a TSH of two,

00:46:16.330 --> 00:46:18.370
but I feel good at a TSH of one.

00:46:18.370 --> 00:46:20.680
So when, five years from
now, you have a baby,

00:46:20.680 --> 00:46:23.530
or something happens and your
TSH shifts and you're, quote

00:46:23.530 --> 00:46:25.630
